# .cursorrules
# Project-wide AI coding rules for Deep Researcher Agent

style:
  - Use Python 3.10+
  - Code must be modular and production-ready
  - Follow PEP8 and include docstrings for all methods
  - Use type hints everywhere

project_structure:
  - src/
    - __init__.py
    - embeddings.py        # local embedding generation
    - vectorstore.py       # FAISS/Chroma storage & retrieval
    - reasoning.py         # multi-step reasoning logic
    - summarizer.py        # combines multi-doc results into report
    - query_handler.py     # main interface for user queries
  - data/
    - sample.txt           # sample docs for testing
  - main.py                # entry point
  - requirements.txt       # dependencies
  - README.md              # documentation

dependencies:
  - sentence-transformers   # for embeddings
  - faiss-cpu              # vector store
  - langchain              # for retrieval + reasoning chains
  - pypdf2                 # PDF loading
  - rich                   # for CLI formatting
  - reportlab              # for exporting to PDF

rules:
  - Do not use any external web search API (Google, Bing, SerpAPI, etc.)
  - All embeddings must be generated locally (SentenceTransformers)
  - Retrieval must be handled via FAISS or Chroma
  - Responses should explain reasoning steps when asked
  - Include a CLI interface for user interaction
  - Add option to export answers in PDF or Markdown
